==English==

===Noun===

'''shin''' (plural: [[shins]])

# The twentysecond letter of the [[Hebrew]] alphabet, [[&#1513;]].

===Etymology===

* From [[Old English]] [[shine]], [[schine]], [[Anglo-Saxon]] [[scina]]
* Akin to [[Dutch]] [[scheen]], [[w:Old High German|Old High German]] [[scina]], [[German]] [[schiene]], [[schienbein]], [[Danish]] [[skinnebeen]], [[Swedish]] [[skenben]].  
* Comparable to [[Chine]]

===Noun===

'''shin''' (plural: [[shins]])

# The front part of the leg below the knee; the front edge of the shin bone; the lower part of the leg; the shank.

===Verb===

'''shin''' ([[shinned]], [[shinning]], [[shins]])

# To climb a mast, tree, rope, or the like, by embracing it alternately with the arms and legs, without help of steps, spurs, or the like; -- used with up; as, to '''shin''' up a mast.

